web_snippets: Vicky is the Director of the Research Centre for Arts and Wellbeing and an internationally known academic and researcher in the arts and arts psychotherapies.
Vicky Tsai (born 1978) is an American businesswoman who is a co-founder of Tatcha, a skincare company based on Japanese beauty rituals.
Vicky was the CEO/President of Frontenac Community Mental Health and Addiction Services (FCMHAS) from 1982 – 2015.
